<br>
BUG- not all alignment options were listed for all classes when you did /align at level 10.<br>
BUG- some advertised alignment options were disallowed by the client<br>
BUG- you COULD group with an evil if you were a good and you COULD heal them... <br>
BUG- some races were given no choice at all (Halflings, Ogres, Darkelves)... some INTELLIGENT races were given no choice. (Flag of disbelief)<br>
LOGISTICAL PROBLEM- GMs, CSRs, and Guides could not change alignment once set.<br>
<br>
There were dozens of other extrapolative problems (like bugs in some zone with corpse summoning) and other logical problems (my laundry list of flags of disbelief).<br>
<br>
Then there is also the HUGE problem of 'my good vs your good.' Verant's vision of good is actually light skinned vindictive... why would TRULY good people deny someone aid?<br>
<br>
Bobmato's idea would have been the best solution... but at the same time it would be difficult to code and implement... and i couldn't imagine what kind of bugs would occur from it.<br>
<br>
However, back to the main point: the nature of the change... The alignment system had problems that was driving people from the server in droves. The population was plummeting and it was locking people into the 'exception classes' (neutral clerics) and therefore REDUCING roleplaying.<br>
<br>
I think that server viability was much more important than the badly done artificial illogical constraints on roleplay. I also still believe that the only way that we can actually BE a RP server is to continue running player RP events, continue RPing by example and not by insult, and continue to keep an open mind about other people's ideas of RP... DESPITE any personal problems we have with them. <p>Nakath<BR>
